<subSubSection pageId="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,781,1058]" pageId="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,961,986]" pageId="5">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[332,602,961,986]" pageId="5" refString="Pachelle, P. P. G., Anker, A., Mendes, C. B. &amp; Bezerra, L. E. A. (2016) Decapod crustaceans from the state of Ceara, northeastern Brazil: an updated checklist of marine and estuarine species, with 23 new records. Zootaxa, 4131 (1), 1 - 63. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4131.1.1" type="journal article">
Pachelle 
<emphasis box="[444,510,961,986]" italics="true" pageId="5">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
reported some morphological divergences between specimens from northeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[300,368,997,1022]" name="Brazil" pageId="5">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[588,647,998,1022]" name="United States of America" pageId="5">USA</collectingCountry>
. The authors suggested that a more detailed comparison (including molecular data) is necessary to clarify these divergences.
</paragraph>
